'''''Pocket World''''' (previously known as ''Pokémon World'') was an unofficial British video games [[magazine]] published monthly by [[Imagine Publishing]] which focused mainly on the [[Pokémon]] franchise of video games, [[Pokémon Trading Card Game|trading cards]] and [[Pokémon (anime)|anime]]. The magazine also featured news and reviews for games on all platforms. At issue 125, the magazine changed its title from ''Pokémon World'' to ''Pocket World'' and featured more information on franchises such as [[Yu-Gi-Oh!]], [[Skylanders]] and [[Bakugan]], despite this change, Pokémon still was the magazine's main focus.

Issue 174 which came out in 2015 was its final issue.

Unrelated: Pocket World: island of adventure. Google Play game.

