{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}} {{Use British English|date=April 2016}} {{Infobox football biography | name = William Bradbury | image = | caption = | fullname = William Henry Bradbury | birth_date = 1884<ref name="kent"/> | birth_place = [[Sudbury, Derbyshire]], England<ref name="kent"/> | death_date = {{Death year and age|1966|1884}}<ref name="kent"/> | height = | position = [[Midfielder|Half-back]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = May Bank | youthyears2 = | youthclubs2 = Newcastle Swifts | years1 = 1903–1907| clubs1 = [[Port Vale F.C.|Burslem Port Vale]]| caps1 = 12| goals1 = 0 | years2 = | clubs2 = Fegg Hayes| caps2 = | goals2 = | years3 = 1910–1911| clubs3 = [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke]]| caps3 = 28| goals3 = 0 | years4 = 1911| clubs4 = [[Aberdare Athletic F.C.|Aberdare]]| caps4 = | goals4 = | years5 = 1911–1913| clubs5 = [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]]| caps5 = 7| goals5 = 2 | years6 = | clubs6 = [[Scunthorpe United F.C.|Scunthorpe United]]| caps6 = | goals6 = | years7 = 1919–1921| clubs7 = [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]]| caps7 = 67| goals7 = 3 | years8 = 1921–1923| clubs8 = [[Rochdale A.F.C.|Rochdale]]| caps8 = 12| goals8 = 0 | years9 = | clubs9 = [[Burton Town F.C.|Burton Town]]| caps9 = | goals9 = | totalcaps = | totalgoals = }}
'''William Henry Bradbury''' (1884–1966) was an [[English people|English]] [[Association football|footballer]] who played at [[Midfielder|half-back]] for [[Port Vale F.C.|Burslem Port Vale]], [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke]], [[Aberdare Athletic F.C.|Aberdare]], [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]], [[Scunthorpe United F.C.|Scunthorpe United]], [[Rochdale A.F.C.|Rochdale]] and [[Burton Town F.C.|Burton Town]].
==Playing career== Bradbury played for May Bank and Newcastle Swifts, before joining [[Port Vale F.C.|Burslem Port Vale]] in May 1903.<ref name="kent">{{cite book|last=Kent|first=Jeff|title=Port Vale Personalities|publisher=Witan Books|page=39 |year=1996 |isbn=0-9529152-0-0 |id= {{ASIN|0952915200|country=ca}}}}</ref> He made his debut on Boxing Day 1903, in a 3–1 defeat by [[Bristol City F.C.|Bristol City]] at the [[Athletic Ground (Cobridge)|Athletic Ground]].<ref name="kent"/> He played three further [[Football League Second Division|Second Division]] games in the rest of the [[1903–04 Burslem Port Vale F.C. season|1903–04]] season, and was used as an emergency player in the [[1904–05 Burslem Port Vale F.C. season|1904–05]], [[1905–06 Burslem Port Vale F.C. season|1905–06]], and [[1906–07 Burslem Port Vale F.C. season|1906–07]] campaigns.<ref name="kent"/> The club then went into financial meltdown and [[liquidation]], at which point he was released.<ref name="kent"/> He joined Fegg Hayes and then moved on to [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke]], playing 28 Birmingham & District League / [[Southern Football League|Southern League]] games for the "Potters" in the [[1910–11 Stoke F.C. season|1910–11]] season.<ref name="kent"/> He later played for [[Aberdare Athletic F.C.|Aberdare]], [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]] (in two spells), [[Scunthorpe United F.C.|Scunthorpe United]], [[Rochdale A.F.C.|Rochdale]] and [[Burton Town F.C.|Burton Town]].<ref name="kent"/>
